PLACEHOLDER_FAQ_TITLE: Frequently Asked Questions About Our Blockchain Analysis App
ACCORDION_ANSWER_1: Our app allows you to analyze and gain insights from new blockchain data as it gets added to the network. It helps monitor and understand the latest transactions, contracts, and activity.
ACCORDION_ANSWER_2: We connect directly to blockchain nodes and parse the new data as it gets mined and added to the distributed ledger. Our algorithms then analyze this data based on customizable rulesets and provide visualizations and reports.
ACCORDION_ANSWER_3: Currently we support analysis of Ethereum, Bitcoin, and several other major blockchain networks. We are constantly working to add support for more networks based on user demand.
ACCORDION_QUESTION_4: Do I need blockchain expertise to use this?
ACCORDION_ANSWER_4: No prior blockchain experience is required. Our user interfaces are designed to be intuitive and accessible to anyone interested in analyzing on-chain data and activities.
FAQ_SUBTITLE_PLACEHOLDER_TEXT: Get answers to common questions about our blockchain data analysis platform
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_ANSWER_TEXT_1: Blockchain analytics refers to the process of analyzing data from blockchain networks to gain insights into transactions, addresses, smart contracts, and overall activity.
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_QUESTION_TEXT_2: Why do I need blockchain analytics?
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_ANSWER_TEXT_2: Blockchain analytics provides valuable intelligence for compliance, security, and business decisions related to blockchain ecosystems. It helps identify risks, trends, and opportunities.
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_ANSWER_TEXT_3: Our platform can analyze data from major blockchains like Bitcoin, Ethereum, and newer networks. This includes transaction details, smart contract code, wallet addresses, and on-chain activity.
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_ANSWER_TEXT_4: We ingest and parse data directly from the blockchain networks using high-performance nodes and indexing systems to ensure comprehensive and reliable insights.
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_ANSWER_TEXT_5: Gain visibility into transaction flows, identify linked addresses, monitor smart contract activity, detect anomalies, and spot emerging trends across blockchain networks.
